laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver is normal in echogenicity without focal lesions. A 1.3 cm anechoic cyst is seen within the dome of the right lobe of the liver. No intrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation; common bile duct measured 5 mm. Gallbladder filled with mobile echogenic shadowing stones, normal wall thickness, no pericholecystic fluid. Right kidney showed no hydronephrosis or stones. Pancreas appears normal.
